<subSubSection id="E1CB653A991F80234ABB5F3EFD546630" pageId="18" pageNumber="431" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="A96E36B1991F80234ABB5F3EFD546630" blockId="18.[139,1069,190,549]" pageId="18" pageNumber="431">
Comments. 
<taxonomicName id="6ED14D32991F80234B3C5F3EFDB96586" authorityName="Bolívar" authorityYear="1879" box="[332,571,380,403]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Brachystethus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricolor">
<emphasis id="9BA5EAA3991F80234B3C5F3EFDB96586" box="[332,571,380,403]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="431">Brachystethus tricolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the sister species of 
<taxonomicName id="6ED14D32991F802349405F3EFC2B6586" authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1903" box="[816,937,380,403]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Brachystethus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vexillum">
<emphasis id="9BA5EAA3991F802349405F3EFC2B6586" box="[816,937,380,403]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="431">B. vexillum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with which shares two synapomorphies and one homoplasy, respectively: venter predominantly red, metasternal carina transversely sulcated and ostiolar rugae short (
<bibRefCitation id="CD404B40991F802349EB5FF4FE9F65FE" author="BARCELLOS, A. &amp; GRAZIA, J." journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa, Auckland" pageId="18" pageNumber="431" pagination="1 - 14" part="256" refId="ref19723" refString="BARCELLOS, A. &amp; GRAZIA, J. 2003. Cladistic analysis and biogeography of Brachystethus Laporte (Heteroptera, Pentatomidae, Edessinae). Zootaxa, Auckland, 256: 1 - 14." title="Cladistic analysis and biogeography of Brachystethus Laporte (Heteroptera, Pentatomidae, Edessinae)" type="journal article" year="2003">
<subScript id="355534F4991F802349DD5FFEFB8C65D9" attach="left" box="[941,1038,444,460]" fontSize="7" pageId="18" pageNumber="431">BARCELLOS</subScript>
&amp; GRAZIA, 
<date id="DD6F1071991F80234A935F96FE9F65FE" box="[227,285,468,491]" pageId="18" pageNumber="431" value="2003">2003</date>
</bibRefCitation>
). These characters also separate both species from theremaining species of the genus. 
<taxonomicName id="6ED14D32991F80234A8E5FB3FE6F661D" authorityName="Bolívar" authorityYear="1879" box="[254,493,497,520]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Brachystethus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricolor">
<emphasis id="9BA5EAA3991F80234A8E5FB3FE6F661D" box="[254,493,497,520]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="431">Brachystethus tricolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="6ED14D32991F8023497E5FB3FC05661D" authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1903" box="[782,903,497,520]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Brachystethus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vexillum">
<emphasis id="9BA5EAA3991F8023497E5FB3FC05661D" box="[782,903,497,520]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="431">B. vexillum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by dorsal color with red spots, and quadrangular shape of pygophore.
</paragraph>
